      "possibleIdentity": "Aleksandra Kasuba (born Aleksandra Fledžinskaitė, 1923–2019) was a pioneering Lithuanian-American environmental artist and architect renowned for her innovative use of tensile fabrics to create immersive, large-scale \"environments.\" Active primarily from the late 1950s through the early 21st century, she gained significant recognition in the late 1960s and early 1970s for her visionary approach to spatial design, which rejected rigid right angles in favor of organic, shell-like structures.
